26. A method of assessing a biological sample containing one or more biological molecules having one or more solvent accessible portions and one or more solvent inaccessible portions, the method comprising:
a) acquiring a first subsample and a second subsample of the biological sample, the first subsample and the second subsample containing substantially equivalent concentrations of the one or more biological molecules;
b) introducing a cleavage factor into the second subsample of the biological sample, the cleavage factor configured to alter the one or more biological molecules to expose at least a portion of the solvent inaccessible portions to solvent;
c) oxidizing, by way of a plasma that introduces marker radicals to the first subsample and the second subsample, the one or more biological molecules in the first subsample and the second subsample;
d) subsequent to step c), assessing a difference in oxidization levels between the one or more biological molecules in the first subsample and the second subsample, thereby identifying at least a portion of the one or more solvent inaccessible portions; and
e) generating a report indicating the identification of the at least a portion of the one or more solvent inaccessible portions.

29. A system for modifying a biological molecule, the system comprising:
a sample chamber configured to contain a sample including a biological molecule, the sample chamber comprising a chemically and biologically inert inner surface;
a ground electrode;
a dielectric separating the sample chamber from the ground electrode;
a plasma electrode comprising a plasma source point;
a plasma electrode positioning system;
a power supply; and
a control system in electronic communication with the power supply, the ground electrode, and the plasma electrode, the control system configured to utilize electrical power from the power supply with the plasma electrode and the ground electrode to generate a plasma from the plasma source point, the plasma configured to generate marker radicals suitable for oxidizing the biological molecule.

41. A system for modifying a biological molecule, the system comprising:
a sample chamber configured to contain a sample including a biological molecule, the sample chamber comprising a chemically and biologically inert inner surface;
a plasma jet configured to generate a plasma and direct the plasma into the sample chamber;
a plasma jet positioning system;
a power supply; and
a control system in electronic communication with the power supply and the plasma jet, the control system configured to utilize electrical power from the power supply with the plasma jet to generate a plasma and direct the plasma into the sample chamber, the plasma configured to generate marker radicals suitable for oxidizing the biological molecule.
